During Fall 2020 Remote Learning semester the Food Service Department will prepare Breakfasts & Lunches for any enrolled PreK - 12th grade student at no cost to you!

We understand *you will have to plan a week ahead* when ordering your meals. In order to have enough food we must leave space between when you order so we can have the items in stock.

This order form is for the WEEK OF AUG 31 - SEPT 4!!!
(where is the Aug 24-28 form? it is closed no longer accepting orders)

Meals must be ordered online - a week ahead of time! (by August 29)
Meals must be picked up daily.

Google form link www.mr238.org
Please direct questions to the Food Service Department 734-3300 or email tallen@mr238.org

Parents, information from your student's school and teacher is on it's way to you... or has already been sent out!

Don't miss an announcement! Update your email & cell phone number!
Keep in mind the TylerSIS program works a lot with email! Make sure you have added @mr238.org to your safe senders / important / contacts list.

HELPFUL TIP: as some families are building support networks during Remote Learning you can put a babysitter, family member and caregiver phone numbers/email (depending on contact type) in Tyler. This may be helpful for communication.

Questions? Contact your student's teacher or school office for assistance in updating Tyler or understanding how to receive school messages.

REMEMBER: Check https://www.mr238.org/news/what_s_new/stay_in_the_know for the District Communication Plan

August 5 at 6:54 PM ·

Titan Families -
At Monmouth-Roseville School District, we want to ensure that all students have access to meals while we are doing a Remote Learning schedule.

Therefore, we will be offering a meal pickup option for enrolled students who are scheduled for remote learning.

The school district is still qualifies for free meals through the Community Eligibility Provision, so there is no cost to you.

For planning purposes, at this time we ask that you please fill out this survey Remote Meal Service to allow our department to get an estimate of how many remote learning families would be interested in the pick-up meal service option.

A future link will provide you with information to formally order meals.

If you have any questions you can leave your comment on the survey

SURVEY LINK https://forms.gle/5X64NtXR1eAsAgoC6

post_text:
***Update***

Parents, your student's school will be sending you a survey via School Messenger. To ensure you get the survey please:
1. make sure your phone and email are updated in TylerSIS
2. make sure you have added @mr238.org to your "Safe Senders" list
3. update your preferences in School Messenger (see https://www.mr238.org/for_parents/school_messenger_alert_system ) for details.

**Please listen to ALL 4 questions (if you answer by phone).
**If your answers are incomplete the system MAY call you back.
***The survey will expire if either parent or guardian responds (only 1 per household is needed)
****This survey will help us plan for August 19. We understand your responses may be updated as back to school gets closer.

post_text: Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) provides nutritional resources to families who have lost access to free or reduced-price school meals due to school closures. Families will receive money on a new or existing EBT card to help fill the school meals gap. The average benefit will be $5.70/day per student, retroactive to when school initially closed. More info here https://frac.org/pebt
shared_text:
FRAC.ORG
Pandemic EBT - Food Research & Action Center
text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) provides nutritional resources to families who have lost access to free or reduced-price school meals due to school closures. Families will receive money on a new or existing EBT card to help fill the school meals gap. The average benefit will be $5.70/day per student, retroactive to when school initially closed. More info here https://frac.org/pebt

FRAC.ORG
Pandemic EBT - Food Research & Action Center

Carl Sandburg College
April 28 at 2:52 AM ·

Students interested in joining Carl Sandburg College’s TRIO Sandburg TRIO Upward Bound or TRIO Sandburg Upward Bound Math-Science programs for the 2020-21 academic year can apply online through an extended deadline of May 15.

Students from Galesburg CUSD #205, Blue Bullets, Abingdon-Avon CUSD #276 and ROWVA CUSD #208 can apply online here for Upward Bound and UBMS: https://bit.ly/3aDEB88

Students from Monmouth-Roseville School District #238 interested in UBMS should apply here: https://bit.ly/2xVfY9R

Applicants must be in grades 8-10 at select area school districts; be a first-generation (neither parent with whom they live has a bachelor’s degree), college-bound student; and/or meet income or academic guidelines. DETAILS: https://bit.ly/2yRZEXy

This is the Monmouth-Roseville School District with a reminder to our parents that school will release early on Friday, February 14th for teacher in-service.

The Monmouth AM Pre-K class and Roseville Pre-K will release at 10:50

There is no PM Pre-K class in Monmouth

The junior high will release at 11:05

The high school will release at 11:10

Lincoln, Harding and Central will release at 11:30

There is also no school on Monday, February 17th in observance of President’s Day.

Have a safe and enjoyable weekend.
